Orchestrates the status tracker: loads and saves the JSON store at a configurable path, appends new tasks, and keeps the rendered `docs/STATUS.md` view in sync by writing both files together in `save()` so the markdown view can never lag behind the JSON source of truth.

`load()` reads and deserializes the JSON array of rows; `save()` writes the store as pretty-printed JSON (with trailing newline for git) and immediately re-renders the markdown view from it in the same step. The `add_task()` command validates impact and difficulty enums, appends a single row to the store (never reordering), then calls `save()`. The `list()` command is read-only, returning a priority-sorted view. The `render()` command re-syncs the markdown after manual edits to the JSON store — the operator has authority to edit/reorder/delete rows directly, but the view catches up here. The `migrate()` bootstrap parses an existing markdown table (via `ctx_core::status_table::parse_rows`) into the JSON store once, and refuses to run if the store already has content.

All I/O is abstracted through the `Fs` trait, and all file operations are synchronous; the crate uses serde for JSON (pretty-printed to stay diffable).